[Print](https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/company/corporate-trends/big-threat-looms-on-airtel-jio-as-vodafone-confirms-talks-on-merger-with-idea/printarticle/56869589.cms)

Comment

Synopsis

The merger of British giant Vodafone and the Aditya Birla Group co Idea —No. 2 and No. 3, respectively — can change the recent telecom game.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

![Image 3](https://img.etimg.com/thumb/msid-56869589,width-300,height-225,imgsize-193125,resizemode-75/.jpg)ET Bureau

NEW DELHI: The biggest consolidation in India’s telecom sector is officially underway with UK’s [Vodafone](https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/vodafone-idea-ltd/stocks/companyid-3154.cms) Group Plc and the KM Birla-owned Idea Cellular confirming they are in initial talks to merge their businesses in a cashless deal which could create the country’s largest mobile phone operator by subscribers and revenue market share.  
  
 While the two companies did not give any details, the statements issued by the two parties suggest that Birla wants equal rights and that Vodafone will hold 50% or less in the merged entity. Vodafone will be issued fresh shares of Idea, which will continue to be listed.  

  
If the merger between India’s No 2 and No 3 telcos materialises, the combined entity will knock off [Bharti Airtel](https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/bharti-airtel-ltd/stocks/companyid-2718.cms) from the top slot for the first time in over 15 years and with its scale, size and synergies, present a strong response to Reliance Jio’s formidable challenge.  

  

![Image 4: Image article boday](https://img.etimg.com/photo/msid-42031747/et-logo.jpg)

  
  
The merger will result in the Indian telecom landscape being dominated by three strong private firms along with the state-owned BSNL.  

